Two aspects of brain structure make it difficult to transfer our subjective experience to that of animals.
On the one hand, the circuits almost always associated with the human consciousness include the lateral prefrontal cortex (because of its involvement in the short-term memory and in the execution / control functions).
This broad region is much more developed in man than in the other primates and seems to be completely absent from other creatures.
