Actress Heather Locklear was arrested for driving under the effects of an unknown drug.
The actress Heather Locklear, known for the role of Amanda in the series "Melrose Place", was arrested this weekend in Santa Barbara, California for driving under the effects of an unknown drug.
One witness observed how she tried to get out of her parking space in Montecito in a rather strange way, California traffic police spokesman reported to the magazine 'People'.
The witness told in detail that Locklear 'pressed the accelerator after 16:30 and made a lot of noise by trying to move her car backwards or forwards out of the parking space, and as she drove backwards, she grabbed her sunglasses a few times.'
A little later, the witness saw that the actress probably didn't realize at the beginning that Locklear stopped on a nearby street and got out of the car.
The witness was the person who notified the emergency service because she had 'feared to live around Locklears'.
When the police patrol arrived, they found the actress sitting in her car, standing across the street blocking traffic.
'She seemed disoriented,' so they took the police to a special drug and alcohol center to take a test.
According to a police spokesman, the actress showed herself cooperative, overindulgence in alcohol was ruled out from the first moment. 'Following the first observations of the officials, we believe that Locklear was under the influence of an unknown drug,' says the spokesman.
Locklear was arrested under suspicion of driving under the influence of an indefinite substance that could not be determined and taken to a local detention centre around 7 p.m.
Two months ago, after treatment, Locklaer was released from the Arizona hospital, where she was treated for anxiety and depression.
