The drivers, who can be relapsed because of the alcohol level, will have to install the 'Alcolock'.
The authority orders that the driver who had three official penalties for the alcohol level installs in his car this system, which forbids him to start the car in a drunken state. If he is alcoholized, then the car does not start.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the report of the Attorney General. According to her, it is a pilot project, which will last for a year.
The purpose is the rehabilitation of the driver, which is why he gets a course for the re-education of traffic behaviour.
In addition to the Attorney General's Office, experience has shown that the Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for the Safety of Automobiles will participate.
According to statistics, between 30-75% of motorists, who were reported more than once because of driving under the influence of alcohol, returned to driving.
The 'alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system associated with the car, it measures the alcohol content in the exhaled air and prevents autostarting when the driver has made alcohol test; or when an alcohol concentration is determined which is higher than allowed.
It costs more than EUR 1 000, the costs are borne by the person who imposes the sanction.
In this context, a study conducted in the US in 2007 has shown that cars equipped with these devices prevent up to 65% of the standard violations in the first year after its introduction.
In Spain, 115 lives are expected to be saved each year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to tackle this behaviour before it becomes a criminal offence.
And in order to facilitate their implementation, a legislative reform can be implemented by ordinary means, and yet a reform of the Basic Law is called for, which is necessary for the prosecution process.
The device is still not available in Spanish markets, in no business, although it has already been installed in some commercial vehicles and public transport vehicles.
Tomorrow of all days, the House of Deputies will vote on the initiative of the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party, which proposes to install this system in school buses, which has already been done in France.
