A closer look at the study shows that in Milan, a sleeping space in the Brianza district is needed for about 450 euros; a single room starts at 650 euros (in the Bande Nere district) and ends at 800 euros in the Lambiate, Udine and Fiera districts, or even 900 euros in the Vittoria district.
In Florence, a sleeping place costs an average of 350/400 euros, a room 700.
In Bologna, where the students concentrate in the neighborhoods around the university, 250/280 euros are needed for a sleeping place, 370 to 500 for a single room.
In Rome, the prices in the neighbourhoods around the university are around 600 euros for a single room, 450 for a sleeping place in a double room.
Only a little deeper are the rents in the districts around the other universities of Rome: 550 euros in Ostiense and Cinecittà.
